contentrichtext.text: '''Udo''' may refer to: ==People== *[[Udo (Obotrite prince)]] (died 1028) *[[Udo Dirkschneider]] (born 1952), heavy metal vocalist *[[Udo Jürgens]] (born 1934), Austrian composer and singer *[[Udo Kasemets]] (born 1919), Estonian-Canadian composer *[[Udo Kier]] (born 1944), German actor *[[Udo Lattek]] (born 1935), German football manager *[[Udo Lindenberg]] (born 1946), German rock musician and composer *[[Udo Mechels]] (born 1976), Belgian musician *[[Udo Suzuki]] (born 1970), Japanese comedian *[[Udo Proksch]] (1934–2001), businessman, industrialist, and murderer *[[Udo of Aachen]], fictional 13th century monk, created as a 1999 April Fool's hoax *[[Udo von Woyrsch]] (1895–1983), high-ranking Nazi SS officer ==Places== *[[Udo, Miyazaki]], a town in Kyūshū, Japan *[[Mount Udo]], a hill overlooking [[Shimizu-ku, Shizuoka]], Japan *[[Udo, Burma]] *[[Udo Island]], an islet off [[Jeju Island]], [[South Korea]] ==Other== *[[Ultra Density Optical]], a disk format for data storage able to store 60GB on 5.25" optical disk using blue laser technology. *The ''udo'', a Japanese flowering plant named ''[[Aralia cordata]]'' *[[U.D.O.]], 1987 band formed by Udo Dirkschneider *[[United Dance Organisation]], Europe's largest street dance organisation. ==See also== * [[Odo (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
